In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch, sugar, bouillon, dill, salt, lemon peel and pepper. Stir in water and lemon juice until blended; set aside. In a large nonstick skillet or wok, stir-fry the shrimp, mushrooms, celery, yellow pepper and onions in oil for 5 minutes. Add the peas; stir-fry 1-2 minutes longer or until crisp-tender. Stir bouillon mixture; add to skillet. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve with rice.